<DOC><DOCNO> ZF310-614-199 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 614 199</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  April 16 1991 v5 n15 p19(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Macweek 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>AutoMizer logs automobile details. (stack and paper-based datamanagement system from Four Peaks Intelligent Systems Inc.)andO;(tracking details of automobile management) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Cohen, Raines.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Four Peaks Intelligent Systems (Product introduction).andO;Product:   AutoMizer (Hypertext software) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     AutomobilesStackwareData Base Management SystemsProduct IntroductionSoftware Packages.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Raines CohenandM;Chandler, Ariz.andP;  -- Keeping track of the details of automobile management --gas mileage, warranties, service and tax records -- can run you down.andP;  Anduntil Apple's notebooks hit the scene late this year, packing a Mac in theback is rarely practical.andM;But Four Peaks Intelligent Systems now is offering a solution in the form ofa stack- and paper-based record-keeping package called the AutoMizer VehicleManagement System.andM;AutoMizer users can store important receipts, warranties and maps.andP;  They canenter mileage, registration, warranty information and notes by hand into anylon-bound journal and organizer offered as an option with the software.andM;When the data is later entered into the stack, it can create interactiveefficiency and cost plots, reports on tax-deductible use andpreventive-maintenance reminders.andP;  The software works with HyperCard 1.2.x,as well as Version 2.0.andM;AutoMizer sells for $30 with the software or $10 without.andP;  MS-DOS and Windowsversions are available as well.andM;AutoMizer is Four Peaks' second Mac product.andP;  OPTDES for the Mac, ported froma leading non-linear optimization tool on other platforms, helps engineersdesign large and complex models.andM;Four Peaks Intelligent Systems is at P.O. Box 1837, Chandler, Ariz.andP;  85244.andO;Phone (602) 839-8774 or (800) 553-0363.andO;</TEXT></DOC>